# SEDust -- size-integrated scattering matrix,
# randomly oriented DH21 astrodust spheroids.
#   P = 0.20, f_Fe = 0.00, axis ratio b/a = 1.4 (oblate)
#   size distribution: data/release/size_distribution.dat,
#     astrodust column, C_sca-weighted average over sizes.
#
# Randomly oriented particles with a plane of symmetry have
# six independent scattering-matrix elements:
#     [ F11  F12   0    0  ]
#     [ F12  F22   0    0  ]
#     [  0    0   F33  F34 ]
#     [  0    0  -F34  F44 ]
# Theta is the scattering angle in degrees, 0 = forward.
#
# Normalization (Mishchenko/Hovenier, as produced by MATR):
#   (1/2) * integral_{-1}^{+1} F11 d(cos Theta) = 1,
#   so F11 = 1 everywhere for isotropic scattering.
#   F22, F33, F44, F12, F34 are NOT divided by F11.
#   Degree of linear polarization for unpolarized incident
#   light is -F12/F11.  Multiply F_ij by C_sca (given per
#   block, in um^2 per H) to recover absolute units.
#
# Blocks are separated by a "# lambda =" line; each block
# has 181 rows at Theta = 0, 1, ..., 180 degrees.
#
#
# lambda [um]   =   3.6000000E-01
# m =   1.5779682E+00  + i   5.7513181E-02
# Cext/H [um^2] =   3.8237541E-14
# Csca/H [um^2] =   2.8539133E-14
# albedo        =   7.4636422E-01
# g = a1(2)/3   =   7.1120467E-01
# g (Csca-wtd single-size, cross-check) =   7.1120467E-01
# Lmax          = 122
# alpha_1(0) (exactly 1 by construction) =   1.00000000165071E+00
# (1/2)int F11 dcos on this 1-deg grid   =   1.0003496E+00
#   (differs from 1 only by trapezoid error on the
#    forward peak; alpha_1(0) is the exact statement)
# van der Mee & Hovenier test: SATISFIED
